WOULD BE NICE:

    -------------------------------------------

    Perhaps SequenceBuffer<T> is a better name than NetworkBuffer<T>

    -------------------------------------------

    Move connection stuff out of protocol into its own library

    This way network stuff can depend on serialization support, without circular dependency.

    -------------------------------------------

    Now that quaternion is nice and cleaned up and derived from vec4f, talk to
    Mikko from vectorial to see if he wants to incorporate it into the library.

    -------------------------------------------

    Network serialize layer #ifdef WITH_VECTORIAL could provide native support
    for serializing vectorial types.

    ------------------------------------------- 

    Once interpolation and extrapolation is working, strip out everything from the view
    *except* for the smoothing (eg. error reduction for position and orientation)

    Interpolation and extrapolation will always be done separately from the view

    Simplify the view as much as possible

    -------------------------------------------

    Simplify the cube simulation as much as possible

    We don't need any of the activation/deactivation support anymore

    This should radically simplify everything

    -------------------------------------------

    Can probably do without the default constructor for all serializable objects

    This way a macro could just define the struct, and the user could setup defaults
    in-place at declaration, eg. int num_objects = 0;

    Would make event and message definitions much clearer.

    -------------------------------------------

    Would be cool to have "settings" per-demo.

    These settings would generally be remembered across initialize/shutdown,
    eg. rotation yes/no for the stones PBR mode would be remembered after backspace.

    -------------------------------------------

    Rename m_internal to m_cubes and use m_internal consistently for demo inner class.

    -------------------------------------------
    
    Bring back all the virtual go physics demos as it was being built back up

    They were really fun, especially the spinning stone controls, repeated drops etc.

    Just need to get wireframe rendering back, shouldn't be too hard.

    -------------------------------------------

    Quat4f should be converted to behave like other vectorial types, eg. x(), y() etc. not public x,y,z,w floats.

    Should integrate the quat implementation into the vectorial library.

    --------------------------------------------

    Should probably clean up the whole "RealSlidingWindow", vs. "SlidingWindow" thing.
    
    SlidingWindowWithHoles?

    --------------------------------------------

    Network protocol "Sliding Window" is not a real sliding window.

    A real sliding window doesn't have any holes.

    Real sliding window has sequence at head and trailing ack sequence and no holes.
    
    -------------------------------------------

    Would actually be cooler if display settings could be passed in on the command line,
    eg. -width -height, -windowed -fullscreen and so on.

    This would allow me to fine tune display settings on a per-premake shortcut basis,
    rather than continually editing and recompiling Game.cpp to change width/height.

    -------------------------------------------

    Idea: the quick console starts at the top center of the screen and grows centered?

    -------------------------------------------

    Idea. If a body has energy below some minimum amount,
    don't allow it to transmit interaction.

    Should stop the case where cubes in a big stack never come to rest
    and stay red, and then wake up other cubes while visually not moving 
    at all.

    This would however lead to non-red colored cubes at rest on top of the player cube.

    Is this desired? It's probably the best option.

